  "text": "As an example of PIS pursued by MRs, the production of high grade hydrogen from natural gas steam reforming reaction (the first source of hydrogen production at industrial scale [CITATION_1] ) is conventionally realized by means of a multi-stages process, Figure 3A ; on the contrary, the utilization of a MR housing a hydrogen perm-selective membrane makes the combination of the reaction process for generating hydrogen and its purification in a single device without needing further hydrogen separation stages possible, Figure 3B . ",
